Translation rule

Your translation engine can now use this as its deepest check:

A translation is valid if it preserves the source set of CCDs:
	•	the important distinctions
	•	the governing boundaries
	•	the operative consequences

That is a much sharper audit than “does it feel similar?”

⸻

Market rule

Your market system can also use it:

An artifact has value when it packages one or more CCDs that others can reuse.

That means artifacts are not just files.
They are containers for reusable consequential distinctions.

⸻

Atlas rule

The Atlas can map artifacts by shared CCDs.

Then markets cluster not just by topic, but by:
	•	similar distinctions
	•	similar constraints
	•	similar consequence patterns

That’s stronger than keyword grouping.

That’s structural grouping.

